title: Rubbish truck crashes into house in Lower Hutt
text:
Rubbish truck crashes into house in Lower Hutt Last updated 10:55, February 22 2017 NZN VIDEO 
RAW VISION: A Waste Management rubbish truck ended up stuck after slamming a house in Lower Hutt. 
A rubbish truck crashed into a Lower Hutt house, with the two people in the truck and the person in the house escaping injury. 
Police said the crash happened on Maungaraki Road shortly after 9am on Wednesday. 
Do you know anything about this incident? Email NICHOLAS BOYACK/FAIRFAX NZ 
A rubbish truck crashed into a house on Maungaraki Rd, Lower Hutt. 
The truck rolled down a long driveway and into the house. 
Wellington Free Ambulance staff attending as a precaution. The Police Commercial Vehicle Investigation Unit has been notified and will be investigating.
